<DOC><DOCNO>WSJ910131-0151</DOCNO><DOCID>910131-0151.</DOCID><HL>   McDonnell Douglas   Gets Missile Contract</HL><DATE>01/31/91</DATE><SO>WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), PAGE C2</SO><CO>   MD GD GE GM TRN</CO><IN>AEROSPACE (ARO)</IN><GV>DEFENSE DEPARTMENT (DEF)</GV><LP>   WASHINGTON -- McDonnell Douglas Corp. won a $253.9 millioncontract for 240 Tomahawk sea-launched cruise missiles.                                                                                                       </LP><TEXT>   General Dynamics Corp. was given a $188.6 million Navycontract for 160 Tomahawk sea-launched cruise missiles.                                                                                                          Halter Marine Inc. got a $91.8 million Navy contract fortwo oceanographic survey ships.                                                                                                          Science Applications International Corp. was given a $15.5million Air Force contract for space experiments.                                                                                                          General Electric Co. got $11.7 million in Navy contractsfor shipboard fire-control equipment and for aircraftsearch-and-track systems.                                                                                                          General Motors Corp. received an $11.3 million Air Forcecontract for the advanced-engine gas-generator program.</TEXT></DOC>